OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FTech firms told to do      
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fbetter on child abuse      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fimages                     
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The government is giving Ofcom extra   
OL,6, tools to ensure tech companies act to  
OL,7, prevent, identify and remove child     
OL,8, sexual abuse and exploitation content. 
OL,10,FThe powers will be introduced through  
OL,11,Fan amendment to the Online Safety Bill,
OL,12,Fwhich aims to police the internet.     
OL,14,FIf the tech firms do not comply, Ofcom 
OL,15,Fwill be able to impose fines of up to  
OL,16,F#18m or 10% of the company's global    
OL,17,Fannual turnover, whichever is higher.  
OL,19,FHowever there is growing concern over  
OL,20,Fhow it will work in practice.          
